gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: Managed_Lands_IDNR_IN is a polygon shapefile that contains managed land areas in Indiana, provided by personnel of the Indiana Natural Heritage Data Center, Indiana Department of Natural Resources (INHDC-IDNR) as of March 4, 2015. Attributes include contact information for land managers, as well as whether the land is open to the general public or if access is restricted. For additional information regarding lands owned by federal agencies, local agencies, and non-profit organizations, as well as conservation easements, persons should contact the IDNR Indiana Natural Heritage Data Center (317-232-4052). The following is excerpted from the metadata provided by INHDC-IDNR for the source shapefile MANAGEDLANDS_DNR_INHD_IN_150304.SHP: ManagedLands_DNR_INHD_IN is a subset of ManagedLandsAll_DNR_INHD_IN, excluding those areas that are listed as conservation easements or listed as closed. ManagedLandsAll_DNR is the Indiana Natural Heritage Data Center Managed Areas dataset. It includes natural and recreation areas which are owned or managed by the Indiana Department of Natural Resources, federal agencies, local agencies, and non-profit organizations. It also includes private lands with Conservation Easements owned by IDNR. NATURAL AREAS THAT ARE NOT OWNED NOR MANAGED BY DNR ARE ADDED AS DATA IS AVAILABLE. IT IS BY NO MEANS A COMPLETE AND COMPREHENSIVE DATASET FOR ALL SUCH AREAS IN THE STATE. The Indiana Natural Heritage Data Center Managed Area Database is a digital, geospatial file containing information on Indiana's significant protected natural areas. All counties in the state are represented.

gmd:purpose.gco:CharacterString: To provide the locations of lands owned or managed by the Indiana Department of Natural Resources as a GIS layer. The following is excerpted from the metadata provided by INHDC-IDNR for the source shapefile MANAGEDLANDS_DNR_INHD_IN_150304.SHP: "This file was created as a statewide inventory of significant natural areas"

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: Updates to original dataset: increase to 1,700 labeled polygons. Most additions were local parks with LWCF funds attached to them. Data from deed record maps (Div. of Engineering) were drawn on USGS Topologic maps and digitized adding to previously existing Managed Areas Database. Process was done by Indiana Department of Natural Resources, Jeff Ewick.
Original dataset created by digitizing from topographic maps in the early 1990s. 1,648 labeled polygons. Process was done by Indiana Department of Natural Resources, Irv Goldblatt.
Polygons with duplicate attributes were merged. Several fields were deleted and new fields were added.

Updated polygons for property owned by the Division of Forestry: 1. man1296 manager = forestry and dedicated =y: 19 records = DedicatedForestry_man1296 2. erase from StateForests [man1296 = Deam Lake, Starve Hollow] = ForestLessSra 3. erase from man1296 Vallonia StateForests Jackson-Washington = newVallonia 4. erase from ForestLessSra DedicatedForestry_man1296 = ForestLessSra_Dedicated 5. delete from man1296 Vallonia, Clark, Selmier, Ferdinand, GS, JW, Martin, MM, OP, Salamonie River State Forest, Francis Slocum State Forest, Yellowwood, Wyandotte, HC 6. add to man1296 ForestLessSra_Dedicated, newVallonia 7. change managers for nature preserves 8. update attributes

BLA personnel received an ESRI shapefile from Indiana Natural Heritage Data Center named "IndianaDNR_ManagedLands.shp" on August 30, 2007. BLA personnel then saved the file as MANAGED_LANDS_IDNR_IN.shp and edited the existing metadata. The following empty or duplicate fields were removed - UNITACRE, SITECODE, DNR_CE.

Queries were used to create a subset of the dataset containing only those lands owned or managed by IDNR. This ensures that IDNR can guarantee the accuracy of the spatial data and attributes. Non-IDNR lands (federal, non-profit, etc.) may be accessed within the entire dataset by request from IDNR, Indiana Natural Heritage Data Center, 317-232-4052.
